problems.title: Euler Totient Function of N
problems.description:
The Euler Totient Function phi(N) is defined as the number of integers x in the range 1 to N such that gcd(x, N) = 1.
You are given a positive integer N. Your task is to compute phi(N).

Input Format:
A single integer N.

Output Format:
Print a single integer, the value of phi(N).
problems.examples:
Sample Input
9

Sample Output
6

Explanation:
The integers in [1,9] that are coprime with 9 are: 1,2,4,5,7,8.
hintsList: If n = p1^e1 * p2^e2 * ... * pk^ek, then phi(n) = n * product over i of (1 - 1/pi). You can implement this using prime factorization up to sqrt(n).
